-- Czech Stocks: CEZ Utility, Komercni Banka Are Active in Prague
-- B y   K r y s t o f   C h a m o n i k o l a s
-- 2012-07-18T15:44:06Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-07-18/czech-stocks-cez-utility-komercni-banka-are-active-in-prague.html
The Czech Republic’s  PX (PX)  stock index
fell 0.7 percent to 901.60 at the close in Prague.  The following were among the most active  equities  in the
Czech market today. Stock symbols follow company names.  CEZ AS (CEZ)  , the biggest Czech power producer, slid 1.2
percent to 728 koruna. The government plans to charge generators
for using the grid, Lidove Noviny newspaper reported today,
citing Pavel Gebauer, an energy official from the Industry and
Trade Ministry.  Komercni Banka  AS (KOMB CP), a unit of Societe Generale SA,
added 1.2 percent to 3,455 koruna, its highest close in more
than a week. Czech banks’ capital and liquidity are strong, the
International Monetary Fund and Moody’s Investors Service said
in separate reports yesterday.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Krystof Chamonikolas in Prague at 
 kchamonikola@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
